<!-- PAGE 4: INTRODUCTION -->
<div class="page-break"></div>
<h1 style="font-size: 20pt;">Chapter 1: Introduction</h1>

<h2>1.1 About Oman</h2>
<p>Oman, officially the Sultanate of Oman, is a country located on the southeastern coast of the Arabian Peninsula in Western Asia. With a rich history spanning over 5,000 years, Oman has developed a unique cultural identity that is reflected in its magnificent forts, castles, and mosques.</p>

<p>The architectural heritage of Oman is particularly notable for its defensive structures, including numerous forts and castles strategically positioned throughout the country. These structures served various purposes, from defense against invasions to administration centers and royal residences.</p>

<h2>1.2 Project Purpose</h2>
<p>This educational website aims to showcase the rich heritage of Omani castles and cultural landmarks through an interactive digital experience. The project serves as both a learning tool and a demonstration of web development skills.</p>

<p>The primary objectives of this project are:</p>
<ul>
<li>To educate visitors about the historical significance of Omani castles</li>
<li>To demonstrate proficiency in multimedia web development</li>
<li>To create an engaging and interactive user experience</li>
<li>To meet the technical requirements of the Digital Media course</li>
</ul>

<h2>1.3 Scope of Project</h2>
<p>The website includes the following key features:</p>
<ul>
<li>Interactive gallery of Omani castles with hover effects</li>
<li>3D interactive Khanjar (traditional dagger) visualization</li>
<li>Image editor with 12 filter effects</li>
<li>YouTube video integration</li>
<li>Web Audio synthesized music</li>
<li>Hidden Easter egg feature</li>
<li>Fully responsive design for all devices</li>
</ul>

